name: Vinegaroon Canyon
description:
Introduction

Very scenic approach in the wash & on the ridge.

Approach

Start off 20-Mule Team Road and go immediately over the hump to gain your wash. Weave through the wash until a branch left at a small cairn to go up a gulley. Then cross over a ridge and drop down into a wash. Head right, down the wash for 3/4 a mile before taking a right up a wash up to a ridge. Go left along this ridge before leaving it right. Reaching the right gulley for the canyon was a little confusing and involved a couple backtracks to stay on GPX route.

Starting the canyon there are two 10' down climbs followed by a mildly-technical down climb by a chockstone. Then another 30' of easy down climbing until the first rappel.

Descent

Anchors may be further back that adds to the rope length. All anchors are cairns:

R1 : 85

R2 : 25

R3 : 20

R4 : 25

R5 : 25

Exit

Red tape
